				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree with the guy who helped, that if you want aggro, you can get it with chants, 300pts a tick is a fair amount of damage.  I have done this once, when a mob had an undebuffable-DS, so I thought I was saving the healer mana by not meleeing.  I have since come to think I should have continued with my melee buff songs as we were melee heavy that group.  If your group lets you and doesn't think you need to be playing haste, DS, mana regen etc in battle, then try it out, just don't make it so you don't get an invite back because they are pissed at you for not meleeing.
<br />

<br />
As for KEI, it is 14 pts a tick.  55 Replenishment is 12 pts a tick.  Yes KEI is better... HOWEVER, replenishment stacks with KEI, so you go from 14 pts a tick to 26.  If you REALLY want to get mana flowing, I sometimes twist replenishment, 32 mana and amp.  That cranks my mana production up to 24 a tick, or the total up to 36 pts a tick.  If you add BST crack to that, it goes up from there, plus folks FT items.  For that special time when one cleric is buffing an entire raid and you are all waiting for one person to get the show on the road.  It is not an every day thing as it's a fairly intricate twist to do it right.
<br />

<br />
As for mana conservation items, there are plenty. But they don't help bards.
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
